name: Evergreen
description: A mystical and vast world with diverse landscapes.

name: Aetheria
description: A floating region in the sky, known for its forests, plains, rivers, and mountains.

name: Dragonica
description: Region filled with ancient dragon lore and mysteries.

name: New Olympia
description: Mountain range occupied by a large dwarven civilization and a multiracial society.

name: Obsidia
description: Region known for its Echoing Forest and Whispering Woods.

name: Raefun
description: A region with varied geography, from plains to mountains and coast.

name: Old Pillar
description: An area known for its historical significance and ancient ruins.

name: Triton
description: The largest merfolk ocean civilization, also an island civilization.

name: Neptune
description: A merfolk civilization located in the sea between continents.

name: Regalis
description: Region with the well-known citadel Areion and the large library of Elderglen.

name: Terah
description: Known as The Land of Judges, includes deserts, plains, and coastal areas.

name: Elysia
description: Mainly plains, known for its egalitarian society and tension with Regalis.

name: Goblin Hollow
description: Network of underground caves and tunnels adjacent to Raefun.

name: Antiqua
description: The cursed former capital of the Empire of Solara, now a barren land.
